  "prompt": "What is achilles tendonitis?",
  "response": "Achilles tendonitis is an overuse injury of the Achilles tendon, the band of tissue that connects the calf muscles at the back of your lower leg to your heel bone. It's common among runners and athletes who participate in sports that require a lot of running, jumping, or sudden starts and stops. The condition is characterized by pain and stiffness along the Achilles tendon, especially in the morning or after periods of inactivity. Other symptoms may include swelling, warmth, or tenderness in the affected area. Treatment often involves rest, ice, compression, elevation (RICE), stretching, physical therapy, and in some cases, medications or surgery. Preventive measures include proper warm-ups, stretching, and using appropriate footwear.",
